What you need to know:

The ministry said 169 more patients had discharged, 83 from hospitals and 86 from home-based care programmes, raising the total number of recoveries to 7,743.Globally, according to Covid-19 case tracker Wordometer,  the number of coronavirus cases was 16,256,472 as of July 26. Deaths numbers 649,354 and the recoveries 9,949,306.The capital city has remained a top hotspot, recording hundreds of cases since the July 6 presidential directive that lifted the cessation of movement order that had locked down hotspot counties. 